Thermophotovoltaic (TPV) cells convert thermal radiation emitted from a thermal source directly into electricity (Fig. 1). The thermal transmitter behaves like a black body. It entirely absorbs radiations received from the heat source. To improve the reflectance and the spectral transmittance of the one-dimensional filter, the structure (TiO2/SiO2 PhC) must correspond to the spectral distribution of the transmitter at high temperature in the corresponding band of the reflectance and transmittance [7, 16]. According to Planck’s law, the spectral power of the radiation of the source at high temperature is [7]:Fig. 1
General diagram of a system TPV17Eλ,T=2πhc2λ5exphcλKT−1,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
